# errors_issues.found — Final Resolution Log

Date finalized: 2026-05-16

## 1) PO print/download were behaving the same and failing to produce usable output

### Resolution
- In `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx`:
  - Kept `handlePrintPurchaseOrder(...)` as dedicated print flow (print window + printable HTML).
  - Kept `handleDownloadPurchaseOrderPdf(...)` as separate downloadable PDF flow.
  - Added `escapeHtml(...)` for print markup safety and `escapePdfText(...)` for PDF stream safety.
  - Updated print timing to invoke `print()` on `printWindow.onload` for render reliability.
  - Added capped-line handling in PDF generation for long content.

### Verification
- Print action and Download action are separate handlers and separate UX outcomes.
- Lint passed.

## 2) Putting an item on hold from PO modal required removing from PO first

### Resolution
- In `app/actions/restock.ts`, updated `putRestockItemOnHold(...)` to support PO-linked items:
  - fetch PO line
  - validate parent PO status (`open` or `placed`)
  - delete PO line
  - subtract line amount from PO total
  - proceed with orphan + on-hold restock item workflow

### Verification
- Action-layer logic no longer enforces manual pre-removal when item is PO-linked.
- Lint passed.

## 3) Need universal dropdown behavior below selector across restock pages

### Resolution
- Standardized `align-top` application across restock UI select controls in:
  - `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx`
  - `components/admin/restock/suppliers-list.tsx`
  - `components/admin/restock/new-restock-request-form.tsx`
  - `components/admin/restock/restock-requests-list.tsx`
- Preserved custom dropdown overlay anchoring via `top-full` in workflow tab search suggestions.

### Verification
- Lint passed.
- Note: native select popup rendering is browser/OS controlled; this is the strongest practical consistency bias in current implementation.

## 4) Upcoming scheduled reorder count should only include open POs (exclude placed)

### Resolution
- Updated count logic in `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx` to require matching scheduled PO with `status === 'open'`.

### Verification
- Count logic now explicitly excludes placed/cancelled/non-open statuses.
- Lint passed.
